Refiloe first rose to fame as a contestant on popular TV music competition Coca-Cola Popstars. She was part of the 2003 winners who formed the group, Adilah.Their first song Sesfikile quickly became a hit, and the group soon become a household name.Refiloe brought some edge to the group, with her unique reggae sound and rapping skills.Unfortunately, the group didn't stay together for long. They all went their separate ways during the height of their career, and focused on their solo projects. Find the hottest celebrity and entertainment news on TshisaLIVE or follow TshisaLIVE on Facebook and Twitter.